The last four of this year’s Champions League begins this Tuesday. Bayern Munich’s Robert Lewandowski remains the highest goal scorer with 14 goals and is now clear in the race to win the Golden Boot. The Polish striker is four ahead of Erling Haaland who is out of the running following Borussia Dortmund’s exit. Lewandowski will come face to face with his nearest competitor, Lyon’s Memphis Depay, who has six goals. His Bayern team-mate, Serge Gnabry, is on seven goals after he scored in their 8-2 demolition of Barcelona. Gabriel Jesus (Man City), Raheem Sterling (Man City) and Dries Mertens (Napoli) all have six goals too. UEFA Champions League leading goalscorers after quarter-final matches: 14: Lewandowski (Bayern Munich) 10: Haaland (Dortmund) 7: Serge Gnabry (Bayern Munich) 6: Depay (Lyon), Gabriel Jesus (Man City), Kane (Tottenham), Mertens (Napoli), Sterling (Man City) 5: Benzema (Real Madrid), Icardi (PSG), Ilicic (Atalanta), Martinez (Inter Milan), Mbappe (PSG), Son (Tottenham)